Hi Lisa-
Apparently, Christine reached out to Yurushka again. I have no idea if this will ever be relevant but I am sharing the mail
response I got from her today with a super bill and a diagnosis code from our sessions. The only reason I think it might be
relevant is that Christine and Yurushka had been secretly meeting before our joint meetings to work on DV strategy. It's a
long story I won't repeat it. But ever since then, Christine has always told me that Yurushka justified their covert
triangulation because our situation was interpreted as DV and presented imminent harm to her and the family. This even
though we were still going on regular fancy dates, were at the absolute peak of our married intimate relations, doing
shrooms together on the weekends, and Yurushak was recommending we all have regular family dinners. Christine has said
Debbie Bayer (our couples counselor) and Dr Mo Brown (parenting plan consultant), have said it's DV too. Then she starts
the threats to use DV in court if I don't go along with whatever her ask is that day. It's a painful pattern.
I'll put on my big boy pants and just deal with it. Lots of crazy stuff is said between us. But, if it ever comes up in a court
setting that we do not want, I thought it might be good to share the actual diagnosis code for the therapy  Yurushka
conducted. Because it seems to officially reflect our obvious martial conflict and not DV. Again, hope this is never relevant.
As I understand:

The diagnosis code "Z63.0" is used to specify problems in a relationship with a spouse or partner to indicate
interpersonal conflicts, misunderstandings, and emotional disconnects in a relationship.
And then "ICD-10" codes that are used to indicate domestic violence are
"Z69.11": Used for encounters for mental health services for victims of spousal or partner abuse
"W86.0XXA": Another code associated with domestic violence
"T74.11XA": A billable/specific ICD-10-CM code that can be used to indicate a diagnosis of adult physical abuse,
confirmed
Attached herewith is the superbill.
Kind regards,
